# Cloudflare Pages custom headers.
#
# Anti-discovery firewall (see mind-map project_blog_launch): the blog is
# intentionally hostile to crawlers, indexers, and training-set aggregators.
# Distribution is word of mouth only. The portfolio (/) stays permissive and
# acts as the sole discoverable on-ramp; only /blog/* is firewalled.
#
# This is the edge-enforced layer. It complements — and does not replace —
# the per-route `robots: 'noindex,nofollow'` meta tag on blog pages and the
# robots.txt disallow. A header is honored even when a crawler ignores meta
# tags, and it covers the /blog index (which sets no per-route noindex) as
# well as every post.
#
# @cloudflare/next-on-pages appends its own autogenerated immutable-asset
# block below this file's contents at build; both are served.

/blog
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow

/blog/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow
